01:28.880 --> 01:30.782
For spies, the hardest part
of operating

01:30.850 --> 01:32.383
in the field
isn't combat.

01:32.451 --> 01:33.651
When bullets are flying,

01:33.719 --> 01:36.020
there's never really time
to think.

01:36.087 --> 01:38.188
But in the quiet hours,
when you're alone,

01:38.256 --> 01:42.060
thinking
is all you can do.

01:48.936 --> 01:50.971
Spies don't make a habit
of holding on to keepsakes

01:51.038 --> 01:52.005
for the same reason
prisoners

01:52.073 --> 01:53.474
serving life sentences

01:53.541 --> 01:57.345
stop seeing visitors.

01:57.413 --> 01:59.773
As much as you might want that
connection to your past life,

01:59.816 --> 02:01.536
there comes a point
when a constant reminder

02:01.551 --> 02:04.454
of what you can never have
is just too painful.

02:08.226 --> 02:10.060
And you can't have
distractions like that

02:10.127 --> 02:12.129
when you have to focus
on a job.

02:29.083 --> 02:31.418
Whoa, that's a good look.

02:31.485 --> 02:32.853
Beard get too hot?

02:32.920 --> 02:34.855
Well, I figure
whatever the next job is,

02:34.922 --> 02:38.058
I shouldn't look like
the guy on the news.

02:38.126 --> 02:39.593
Speaking of,
what is the next job?

02:39.661 --> 02:42.196
We're gonna steal
a truck.

02:42.264 --> 02:44.231
- And the truck's in the bar?
- No.

02:44.299 --> 02:46.434
The gentleman
who's going to help us is.

02:46.502 --> 02:49.204
A local guy I've used before.
He's got his own crew.

02:49.272 --> 02:51.406
If you need a crew,
I have two guys in Miami.

02:51.474 --> 02:54.009
No, that's all right,
thanks.

02:54.077 --> 02:57.280
Let's do it this way.

02:59.750 --> 03:01.084
Mechoso.

03:01.152 --> 03:02.652
Hey,<i>Â¿que pasa?</i>

03:02.720 --> 03:04.221
<i>Bien, bien.</i>

03:06.524 --> 03:07.958
Who's he?

03:08.026 --> 03:10.394
He's just a guy
standing by a table.

03:10.462 --> 03:12.497
So you and your boys,

03:12.565 --> 03:14.265
you can do this job?

03:14.333 --> 03:15.534
I took a look.

03:15.601 --> 03:17.035
We crash the gate,
we hit it hard.

03:17.103 --> 03:18.303
It's no problem.
Okay.

03:18.371 --> 03:21.006
But I do want to discuss
one thing--

03:21.073 --> 03:23.642
my price,
it just went up.

03:23.709 --> 03:24.876
- Did it?
- Yeah.

03:24.944 --> 03:28.314
'Cause I did some,
uh, how do you say?

03:28.381 --> 03:30.116
Research.

03:30.183 --> 03:32.418
That truck
you want to steal,

03:32.486 --> 03:35.588
it belongs to that company
that's all over the news,

03:35.656 --> 03:37.757
the one with the building
that just blew up.

03:37.825 --> 03:39.125
That's none of your business,
Mechoso.

03:39.193 --> 03:40.593
Well, I made it
my business.

03:40.661 --> 03:42.929
I hear they lost a bunch
of satellite computer stuff.

03:42.997 --> 03:44.931
$25 million worth.

03:46.968 --> 03:48.902
You blow up the computers,

03:48.970 --> 03:52.306
they gotta bring in new ones
on a truck,

03:52.374 --> 03:54.776
and you hire Mechoso to steal
the truck--that about right?

03:54.843 --> 03:57.545
Ah.

03:57.613 --> 03:59.414
You got me.

03:59.482 --> 04:01.216
Smart plan, amigo.

04:01.283 --> 04:03.952
- Well, you know, yeah.
- Mm.

04:04.019 --> 04:06.488
But it's not gonna
cost you no $5,000.

04:06.555 --> 04:07.923
No.

04:07.990 --> 04:10.258
It's going to be
12.5 million.

04:10.326 --> 04:11.726
Hmm.

04:11.794 --> 04:13.928
I'm only gonna tell you this
one time.

04:13.996 --> 04:16.231
Okay.

04:16.298 --> 04:17.699
You don't want
to do this.

04:17.767 --> 04:19.968
I think I do.

04:21.737 --> 04:24.639
Or maybe I make my dinero
another way.

04:24.707 --> 04:27.376
There are people who'd pay
to know what I know.

04:27.444 --> 04:30.579
A lot more
than you're offering.

04:36.552 --> 04:40.955
Mechoso, you know me.

04:41.022 --> 04:42.990
You know
I'm a reasonable man.

04:43.058 --> 04:45.360
I just want a little
something extra, Burke.

04:45.427 --> 04:47.928
I think I deserve
a little something extra.

04:47.996 --> 04:49.764
Let me think.
No.

04:57.006 --> 04:58.940
There's your little
something extra.

05:03.346 --> 05:05.380
So...

05:05.448 --> 05:09.084
Tell me about your guys
in Miami.

